<div id="windows-management" v-cloak>
  <div purpose="landing-page-container">
    <div purpose="landing-page-content">
      <div purpose="landing-page-hero">
        <div purpose="page-hero-content">
          <div purpose="page-hero-headings">
            <h4>Windows Device Management</h4>
            <h1>Modern Windows management at enterprise scale</h1>
          </div>
          <div purpose="page-hero-text">
            <p>Enroll, configure, patch, and secure Windows endpoints with full visibility and control. <br>Manage Windows alongside macOS, Linux, iOS, iPadOS, Android, and ChromeOS from one open platform.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="button-row" class="d-flex justify-content-center align-items-center">
            <a purpose="cta-button" class="btn btn-primary" href="/contact">Get a demo</a>
            <animated-arrow-button href="/gitops-workshop">Join a workshop</animated-arrow-button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div><%/* landing-page-hero */%>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="section-heading">
          <h3>Windows fleets are outgrowing legacy management</h3>
          <p>Group Policy, image-based deployments, and point tools were built for the corporate LAN. Today’s Windows endpoints live on coffee shop Wi-Fi, in cloud VMs, and across BYOD programs. The old playbook leaves gaps.</p>
        </div>
        <div purpose="four-column-feature-row">
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Slow, fragile patching</h5>
            <p>WSUS rings and manual repackaging mean CVEs sit unpatched while IT chases packagers.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Tool sprawl</h5>
            <p>Separate consoles for MDM, patching, inventory, EDR, and compliance create duplicate work and licensing waste.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Stale inventory</h5>
            <p>Daily check-ins and CMDBs drift out of date. Auditors and security teams get a snapshot, not the truth.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>ClickOps risk</h5>
            <p>GUI-only changes have no review, no version history, and no easy rollback when a policy breaks production.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="feature-with-image">
          <div purpose="feature-image">
            <img alt="A screenshot of Fleet showing Windows configuration profiles managed as code." src="/images/infrastructure-as-code-feature-image-1-504x378@2x.png">
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-text">
            <h3>One platform for every Windows endpoint</h3>
            <p>Fleet brings modern MDM, software management, vulnerability reporting, and osquery-powered visibility into a single open platform. Apply the same workflows you use for macOS and Linux to your Windows fleet.</p>
            <div purpose="checklist">
              <p>Enroll Windows hosts with Autopilot, Microsoft Entra ID, or manual MDM enrollment</p>
              <p>Deliver configuration profiles using Windows CSPs, defined in XML and version controlled</p>
              <p>Enable BitLocker disk encryption and escrow recovery keys automatically</p>
              <p>Schedule Windows updates with deadlines and grace periods that respect end users</p>
              <p>Run PowerShell scripts on demand or as automated policy remediation</p>
              <p>Track installed software, detect CVEs, and roll out patches across your fleet</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="section-quote">
          <p purpose="quote-text">"Fleet is the best multi-OS MDM on the market currently and is improving daily. Fleet makes sense for me because of their amazing support, transparent and detailed reporting, app updating functionality, self-service, and macOS DDM support."</p>
          <div purpose="quote-author-info">
            <div purpose="quote-author-image">
              <img alt="Fiona Skelton" src="/images/testimonial-author-fiona-skelton-100x100@2x.jpeg">
            </div>
            <div purpose="name-and-title">
              <p purpose="author-name">Fiona Skelton</p>
              <p purpose="author-title">Senior Technology Specialist</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="section-heading">
          <h2>Modern vs. traditional Windows management</h2>
          <p>Fleet treats Windows endpoints like infrastructure. Configurations live in code. Data is live. Every change is reviewable.</p>
        </div>
        <div purpose="two-column-list">
          <div purpose="column-list">
            <h3>Traditional Windows management</h3>
            <div purpose="checklist" style="--list-style: dash;">
              <p>GUI-driven changes with no review or audit trail</p>
              <p>Periodic check-ins and stale inventory data</p>
              <p>Separate tools for MDM, patching, scripting, and compliance</p>
              <p>Vendor lock-in to a single cloud or licensing tier</p>
              <p>Closed source. You cannot inspect or extend what you run</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div purpose="column-list">
            <h3>Fleet on Windows</h3>
            <div purpose="checklist">
              <p>Configuration as code with pull request review and instant rollback</p>
              <p>Live device data from osquery, not yesterday’s report</p>
              <p>One console for MDM, software, vulnerabilities, scripts, and policies</p>
              <p>Self-host, run in your private cloud, or use Fleet-hosted cloud with full feature parity</p>
              <p>Open source under MIT. Audit, contribute, and adapt to your environment</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div purpose="landing-page-section">
        <div purpose="section-heading">
          <h2>Built for Windows at enterprise scale</h2>
        </div>
        <div purpose="feature-row">
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Zero-touch enrollment</h5>
            <p>Connect Fleet to Microsoft Entra ID and use Windows Autopilot to deliver new laptops ready to work, straight from the OEM.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Custom configuration profiles</h5>
            <p>Deliver any Windows CSP setting through Fleet, from Defender controls to start menu layouts, defined in XML and stored in Git.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>BitLocker disk encryption</h5>
            <p>Enforce full-disk encryption, require a PIN if you need it, and escrow recovery keys for help desk and audit workflows.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Windows Update orchestration</h5>
            <p>Set deadlines and grace periods so security patches ship on a predictable cadence without surprising end users.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>PowerShell at fleet scale</h5>
            <p>Run scripts on demand or trigger them automatically through policies. Use the API to integrate with your existing tools.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Software and patch management</h5>
            <p>Maintain a software inventory, detect CVEs, and deploy patches and applications across your Windows fleet from one workflow.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Real-time policies and compliance</h5>
            <p>Author policies in SQL or YAML to monitor compliance continuously. Trigger remediation scripts the moment a host drifts.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>One inventory across every OS</h5>
            <p>See Windows, macOS, Linux, iOS, iPadOS, Android, and ChromeOS in a single console with a consistent data model and API.</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-item">
            <h5>Deploy anywhere</h5>
            <p>Run Fleet on-premise, in AWS, Azure, or GCP, in air-gapped environments, or use Fleet-hosted cloud. Same features, no lock-in.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

  <div purpose="tweets-container" class="container-fluid px-md-0 pb-0 d-flex flex-column justify-content-center">
    <div purpose="section-heading" class="mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="mb-3">What people are saying</h2>
    </div>
  </div>
  <scrollable-tweets :testimonials="testimonialsForScrollableTweets"></scrollable-tweets>

  <div purpose="bottom-gradient">
    <div purpose="page-container" class="container">
      <div purpose="bottom-cta" class="text-center">
        <h4>Windows Device Management</h4>
        <h1>Bring your Windows fleet into one open platform</h1>
        <div purpose="button-row" style="margin-top: 32px;" class="d-flex justify-content-center align-items-center mx-auto">
          <a purpose="cta-button" class="btn btn-primary" href="/contact">Get a demo</a>
          <animated-arrow-button href="/gitops-workshop">Join a workshop</animated-arrow-button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <%/* Cloud city banner */%>
  <parallax-city></parallax-city>
  <modal purpose="video-modal" v-if="modal === 'fleet-in-three-minutes'" @close="closeModal()">
    <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/q1Tm3IBcx24?rel=0&autoplay=1" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe>
  </modal>
</div>
<%- /* Expose server-rendered data as window.SAILS_LOCALS :: */ exposeLocalsToBrowser() %>
